1. DEFINITIONS

1.1. "Community Materials" means the following components made available by
Iternal Technologies, Inc. ("Iternal") under this Community License:

  (a) The Blockify Distillation Service source code and Docker containers
      published in Iternal's public GitHub repositories (currently: the
      blockify-distillation-service/ directory);

  (b) The Blockify Skill for Claude Code source code and associated scripts,
      references, and benchmark tooling (currently: the
      blockify-skill-for-claude-code/ directory);

  (c) Technical documentation published in Iternal's public repositories
      (currently: the documentation/ directory);

  (d) The IdeaBlock XML schema specification and reference documentation;

  (e) Blockify fine-tuned large language model weights designated as
      "Community" models, if and when released by Iternal;

  (f) Sample code, tutorials, Helm charts, Docker configurations, and
      reference implementations published under this license; and

  (g) Any other materials Iternal expressly designates as covered by this
      Community License.

1.2. "Derivative Work" means any modification, enhancement, fine-tune,
adaptation, or work based upon the Community Materials, including but not
limited to fine-tuned model weights, adapted source code, and applications
that incorporate the Community Materials.

1.3. "Competing Product" means any commercial product or service whose primary
purpose is data ingestion, chunking optimization, semantic distillation, or
knowledge-block generation for AI/RAG systems that substantially replicates
the core functionality of the Blockify platform. For the avoidance of doubt:

  (a) Building AI/RAG applications, chatbots, agents, or search systems that
      USE IdeaBlocks as input is NOT a Competing Product;

  (b) Building developer tools, integrations, pipelines, or workflows that
      interface with or extend the Blockify API is NOT a Competing Product;

  (c) Building a commercial product or service whose primary purpose is to
      replicate Blockify's data distillation and IdeaBlock generation
      capabilities IS a Competing Product.

1.4. "Revenue Threshold" means One Million United States Dollars
($1,000,000 USD) in annual gross revenue, calculated as the trailing twelve
(12) months of consolidated worldwide gross revenue of the Licensee and all
Affiliates (as defined below).

1.5. "Affiliate" means any entity that directly or indirectly controls, is
controlled by, or is under common control with the Licensee. "Control" means
ownership of more than fifty percent (50%) of the voting securities or
equivalent ownership interest.

1.6. "Enterprise Materials" means the components of Blockify NOT included in
the Community Materials, including but not limited to: advanced distillation
algorithms (hierarchical, multi-pass, domain-tuned), automated ingestion
connectors (SharePoint, Confluence, Drive, S3, Git), enterprise document
parsers (PDF, DOCX, PPTX, HTML, structured data), role-based access control,
governance dashboards, content lifecycle management, audit logging, compliance
tagging, air-gapped deployment (AirgapAI), hardened pre-built production
containers, SLA-backed support, and any model weights designated as
"Enterprise" or "Commercial."


