  (c) Clearly identify any modifications You made to the Community Materials.

3.2. No Competing Product. You shall not use the Community Materials,
Derivative Works, or knowledge obtained from the Community Materials to build,
train, improve, or operate a Competing Product (as defined in Section 1.3).

3.3. No Misrepresentation. You shall not represent or imply that Your
Derivative Work is an official Iternal product, or that Iternal endorses Your
Derivative Work, without Iternal's prior written consent.

3.4. Model Output Freedom. You may use IdeaBlocks and other outputs generated
by Community Materials freely for any lawful purpose, subject only to the
Competing Product restriction in Section 3.2 and the Revenue Threshold in
Section 4.

3.5. No Hosting as a Managed Service. You may not offer the Community
Materials as a hosted, managed, or "as-a-service" product to third parties
where the primary value delivered is access to the Blockify distillation
service, Blockify models, or IdeaBlock generation pipeline itself.

  (a) Incorporating Blockify outputs (IdeaBlocks) into Your own application,
      product, or service is permitted;

  (b) Using the distillation service internally within Your organization is
      permitted;

  (c) Offering a commercial service that is primarily a wrapper around the
      Blockify distillation service or models for third-party use is NOT
      permitted without an enterprise agreement from Iternal.


4. REVENUE THRESHOLD AND ENTERPRISE LICENSING

4.1. Revenue Threshold. If Your annual gross revenue (including all
Affiliates) exceeds the Revenue Threshold ($1,000,000 USD), You must either:

  (a) Contact Iternal at sales@iternal.ai to negotiate an enterprise license
      agreement; or

  (b) Cease commercial use of the Community Materials within sixty (60) days
      of exceeding the Revenue Threshold.

4.2. Self-Certification. You are responsible for monitoring Your own revenue
and determining when the Revenue Threshold is exceeded. Iternal reserves the
right to request reasonable verification of revenue status from any commercial
user of the Community Materials.

4.3. Grace Period. Upon first exceeding the Revenue Threshold, You have a
grace period of sixty (60) days to either execute an enterprise agreement with
Iternal or cease commercial use. Use during the grace period does not
constitute a breach of this Community License.

4.4. Revenue Calculation. Revenue is calculated based on the Licensee's
consolidated worldwide gross revenue from all sources, not solely revenue
attributable to use of the Community Materials. For entities that are part of
a corporate group, the revenue of all Affiliates is included.

4.5. Enterprise Terms. Enterprise license terms, including scope, pricing,
deployment rights, support levels, and SLAs, are negotiated directly between
the Customer and Iternal. Enterprise terms are not published and are treated
as confidential between the parties. Nothing in this Community License
prescribes or limits the terms of any enterprise agreement.


