7. TERMINATION

7.1. Termination for Breach. This Community License terminates automatically
if You materially breach any of its terms and fail to cure such breach within
thirty (30) days of becoming aware of it (or of receiving written notice from
Iternal, whichever is earlier).

7.2. Termination by Iternal. Iternal may terminate this Community License upon
sixty (60) days' written notice if it determines, in good faith, that Your use
poses a material risk to Iternal's intellectual property, business, or
reputation. This provision is a safety valve for extraordinary circumstances
and is not intended for routine use.

7.3. Voluntary Termination. You may terminate this Community License at any
time by ceasing all use of the Community Materials and destroying all copies
in Your possession or control.

7.4. Effect of Termination. Upon termination:

  (a) You must cease all use of the Community Materials and destroy all copies
      within thirty (30) days;

  (b) Derivative Works that were lawfully distributed to third parties prior
      to termination may continue to be used by those recipients under the
      terms of this Community License;

  (c) Data and outputs (IdeaBlocks) You generated during valid use remain
      Yours.

7.5. Survival. Sections 1 (Definitions), 5 (Intellectual Property),
6 (Disclaimers and Limitations), 7.4-7.5 (Effect of Termination, Survival),
and 8 (General) survive any termination of this Community License.


